35. An ARC may, within the planning period, formulate a plan for realisation of assets which
may provide for one or more of the following measures:
(1) Change in or takeover of the management of the business of the borrower;
(2) Sale or lease of the whole or part of business of the borrower;
(3) Rescheduling of debts payable by the borrower;
(4) Enforcement of security interest in accordance with the provisions of the Act;
(5) Settlement of dues payable by the borrower;
(6) Conversion of any portion of debt into equity of a borrower company.
